text: Éva Kaptur (born 15 November 1987) is a Hungarian athlete competing in sprinting events. ==International competitions== {| |- !colspan="6"|Representing |- |2003 |World Youth Championships |Sherbrooke, Canada |38th (h) |100 m |12.38 |- |2007 |European U23 Championships |Debrecen, Hungary |12th (h) |4x100 m relay |46.44 |- |2009 |Universiade |Belgrade, Serbia |8th |4x100 m relay |46.20 |- |2011 |Universiade |Shenzhen, China |22nd (qf) |200 m |12.02 |- |2012 |European Championships |Helsinki, Finland |22nd (h) |200 m |24.44 |- |2014 |European Championships |Zürich, Switzerland |29th (h) |200 m |24.07 |- |rowspan=2|2015 |European Indoor Championships |Prague, Czech Republic |26th (h) |60 m |7.46 |- |Universiade |Gwangju, South Korea |14th (sf) |200 m |24.16 |- |2016 |European Championships |Amsterdam, Netherlands |13th (h) |4x100 m relay |44.34 |- |2018 |European Championships |Berlin, Germany |13th (h) |4 × 100 m relay |44.15 |} ==Personal bests== Outdoor *100 metres – 11.47 (+1.2 m/s, Budapest 2013) *200 metres – 23.53 (+1.0 m/s, Budapest 2014) Indoor *60 metres – 7.36 (Budapest 2015) *200 metres - 23.99 (Wien 2014) ==References== Category:1987 births Category:Living people Category:Hungarian female sprinters Category:People from Kisvárda Category:Competitors at the 2009 Summer Universiade Category:Competitors at the 2011 Summer Universiade Category:Competitors at the 2015 Summer Universiade
